obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1829)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extend and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1829&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Protection of Plant`
  line `Varieties and Farmers Rights Act, 2001.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 11th November, 2005, ss. 2 to 13 (both inclusive) and ss. 95, 96 and 97, vide notification No. S.O. 1588(E), dated 11th`
  line `November, 2005, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `19th October, 2006, s. 1 and ss. 14 to 94 (both inclusive) vide notification No. S.O. 1797(E), dated 19th October, 2006, see`
  line `Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1830)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1830&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Authority" means the Protection of Plant Varieties and Farmers' Rights Authority`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "benefit sharing", in relation to a variety, means such proportion of the benefit accruing to a`
  line `breeder of such variety or such proportion of the benefit accruing to the breeder from an agent or a`
  line `licensee of such variety, as the case may be, for which a claimant shall be entitled as determined by`
  line `the Authority under section 26.`
  line
  line `(c) "breeder" means a person or group of persons or a farmer or group of farmers or any`
  line `institution which has bred, evolved or developed any variety;`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(e) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Authority appointed under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) "convention country" means a country which has acceded to an international convention for`
  line `the protection of plant varieties to which India has also acceded, or a country which has a law on`
  line `protection of plant varieties on the basis of which India has entered into an agreement for granting`
  line `plant breeders' right to the citizens of both the countries;`
  line
  line `(g) "denomination", in relation to a variety or its propagating material or essentially derived`
  line `variety or its propagating material, means the denomination of such variety or its propagating material`
  line `or essentially derived variety or its propagating material, as the case may be, expressed by means of`
  line `letters or a combination of letters and figures written in any language;`
  line
  line `(h) "essential characteristics" means such heritable traits of a plant variety which are determined`
  line `by the expression of one or more genes of other heritable determinants that contribute to the principle`
  line `features, performance or value of the plant variety;`
  line
  line `(i) "essentially derived variety", in respect of a variety (the initial variety), shall be said to be`
  line `essentially derived from such initial variety when it--`
  line
  line `(i) is predominantly derived from such initial variety, or from a variety that itself is`
  line `predominantly derived from such initial variety, while retaining the expression of the essential`
  line `characteristics that results from the genotype or combination of genotype of such initial variety;`
  line
  line `(ii) is clearly distinguishable from such initial variety; and`
  line
  line `(iii) conforms (except for the differences which result from the act of derivation) to such`
  line `initial variety in the expression of the essential characteristics that result from the genotype or`
  line `combination of genotype of such initial variety;`
  line
  line `(j) "extant variety" means a variety available in India which is--`
  line
  line `(i) notified under section 5 of the Seeds Act, 1966 (54 of 1966); or`
  line
  line `(ii) farmers' variety; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a variety about which there is common knowledge; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any other variety which is in public domain;`
  line
  line `(k) "farmer" means any person who--`
  line
  line `(i) cultivates crops by cultivating the land himself; or`
  line
  line `(ii) cultivates crops by directly supervising the cultivation of land through any other person;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) conserves and preserves, severally or jointly, with any person any wild species or`
  line `traditional varieties or adds value to such wild species or traditional varieties through selection`
  line `and identification of their useful properties;`
  line
  line `(l) "farmers' variety" means a variety which`
  line
  line `(i) has been traditionally cultivated and evolved by the farmers in their fields; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is a wild relative or land race of a variety about which the farmers possess the common`
  line knowledge;
  line
  line `(m) "Gene Fund" means the National Gene Fund constituted under sub-section (1) of section 45;`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(p) "member" means a member of the Authority appointed under clause (b) of sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 3 and includes the member-secretary;`
  line
  line `^3[(q) "prescribed" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to proceedings before a High Court, prescribed by rules made by the High`
  line `Court; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in other cases, prescribed by rules made under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(r) "propagating material" means any plant or its component or part thereof including an intended`
  line `seed or seed which is capable of, or suitable for, regeneration into a plant;`
  line
  line `(s) "Register" means a national Register of Plant Varieties referred to in section 13;`
  line
  line `(t) "Registrar" means a Registrar of Plant Varieties appointed under sub-section (4) of section 12`
  line `and includes the Registrar-General;`
  line
  line `(u) "Registrar-General" means the Registrar-General of Plant Varieties appointed under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section12;`
  line
  line `(v) "Registry" means the Plant Variety Registry referred to in sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(w) "regulations" means regulations made by the Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) "seed" means a type of living embryo or propagule capable of regeneration and giving rise to`
  line `a plant which is true to such type;`
  line
  line ^4*****
  line
  line `(za) "variety" means a plant grouping except micro-organism within a single botanical taxon of`
  line `the lowest known rank, which can be--`
  line
  line `(i) defined by the expression of the characteristics resulting from a given genotype of that`
  line `plant grouping;`
  line
  line `(ii) distinguished from any other plant grouping by expression of at least one of the said`
  line `characteristics; and`
  line
  line `(iii) considered as a unit with regard to its suitability for being propagated, which remains`
  line `unchanged after such propagation,`
  line
  line `and includes propagating material of such variety, extant variety, transgenic variety, farmers variety and`
  line `essentially derived variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (d) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Clauses (n) and (o) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for clause (q) (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Clauses (y) and (z) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1831)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1831&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, establish an authority to be known as the Protection of Plant Varieties and Farmers Rights`
  line `Authority for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of properties, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Authority shall be at such place as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify and the Authority may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, establish branch offices at other places in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall consist of a Chairperson and fifteen members.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) The Chairperson, to be appointed by the Central Government, shall be a person of outstanding`
  line `caliber and eminence, with long practical experience to the satisfaction of that Government especially in`
  line `the field of plant varietal research or agricultural development.`
  line
  line `(b) The members of the Authority, to be appointed by the Central Government, shall be as follows,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Agriculture Commissioner, Government of India, Department of Agriculture and`
  line `Cooperation, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Deputy Director General incharge of Crop Sciences, Indian Council of Agricultural`
  line `Research, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Joint Secretary incharge of Seeds, Government of India, Department of Agriculture and`
  line `Cooperation, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Horticulture Commissioner, Government of India, Department of Agriculture and`
  line `Cooperation, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) the Director, National Bureau of Plant Genetic Resources, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) one member not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India to represent`
  line `the Department of Bio-technology, Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) one member not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India to represent`
  line `the Ministry of Environment and Forests, Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) one member not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India to represent`
  line `the Ministry of Law, Justice and Company Affairs, Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ix) one representative from a National or State level farmers organisation to be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(x) one representative from a tribal organisation to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xi) one representative from the seed industry to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xii) one representative from an agricultural University to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(xiii) one representative from a National or State level womens organisation associated with`
  line `agricultural activities to be nominated by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(xiv) two representatives of State Governments on rotation basis to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(c) The Registrar-General shall be the ex officio member-secretary of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of the Chairperson and the manner of filling the post shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson shall appoint a Standing Committee consisting of five members, one of whom shall be a member who is a representative from a farmers' organisation, to advise the Authority on all`
  line `issues including farmers rights.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chairperson shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and shall be subject to such`
  line `conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line `The allowances for non-official members for attending the meetings of the Authority shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) The Chairperson may resign his office by giving notice thereof in writing to the Central`
  line `Government and on such resignation being accepted, he shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
  line
  line `(10) On the resignation of the Chairperson or on the vacation of the office of the Chairperson for any`
  line `reason, the Central Government may appoint one of the members to officiate as Chairperson till a regular`
  line `Chairperson is appointed in accordance with clause (a) of sub-section (5).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1832)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Meetings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1832&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall meet at such time and place and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings [including the quorum at its`
  line `meetings and the transaction of business of its Standing Committee appointed under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 3] as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the Authority shall preside at the meetings of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) If, for any reason the Chairperson is unable to attend any meeting of the Authority, any member of`
  line `the Authority chosen by the members present shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) All questions which come before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority of`
  line `the votes of the members of the Authority present and voting and in the event of equality of votes, the`
  line `Chairperson of the Authority or in his absence, the person presiding shall have and exercise a second or`
  line `casting vote.`
  line
  line `(5) Every member who is in any way, whether directly, indirectly or personally, concerned or`
  line `interested in a matter to be decided at the meeting shall disclose the nature of his concern or interest and`
  line `after such disclosure, the member, concerned or interested, shall not attend that meeting.`
  line
  line `(6) No act or proceeding of the Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as the Chairperson or a member of the`
  line `Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1833)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Committees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1833&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may appoint such committees as may be necessary`
  line `for the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons appointed as members of the committee under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to`
  line `receive such allowances or fees for attending the meetings of the committee as may be fixed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1834)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Officers and other employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1834&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such control and restriction as may be`
  line `prescribed, the Authority may appoint such officers and other employees as may be necessary for the`
  line `efficient performance of its functions and the method of appointment, the salary and allowances and other`
  line `conditions of service of such other officers and employees of the Authority shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1835)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Chairperson to be Chief Executive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1835&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall be the Chief Executive of the`
  line `Authority and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1836)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `General functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1836&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Authority to promote, by such`
  line `measures as it thinks fit, the encouragement for the development of new varieties of plants and to protect`
  line `the rights of the farmers and breeders.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the measures`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the registration of extant varieties subject to such terms and conditions and in the manner as`
  line `may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) developing characterisation and documentation of varieties registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) documentation, indexing and cataloguing of farmers varieties;`
  line
  line `(d) compulsory cataloguing facilities for all varieties of plants;`
  line
  line `(e) ensuring that seeds of the varieties registered under this Act are available to the farmers and`
  line `providing for compulsory licensing of such varieties if the breeder of such varieties or any other`
  line `person entitled to produce such variety under this Act does not arrange for production and sale of the`
  line `seed in the manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(f) collecting statistics with regard to plant varieties, including the contribution of any person at`
  line `any time in the evolution or development of any plant variety, in India or in any other country, for`
  line `compilation and publication;`
  line
  line `(g) ensuring the maintenance of the Register.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1837)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Authentication of orders, etc., of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1837&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the Authority shall be`
  line `authenticated by the signature of the Chairperson or any other member authorised by the Authority in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1838)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1838&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the`
  line `Chairperson, any member or officer of the Authority subject to such conditions or limitations, if any, as`
  line `may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions (except the power to make regulations`
  line `under section 95) under this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1839)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1839&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In all proceedings under this Act before the Authority or the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Authority or the Registrar, as the case may be, shall have all the powers of a civil court for`
  line `the purposes of receiving evidence, administering oaths, enforcing the attendance of witnesses,`
  line `compelling the discovery and production of documents and issuing commissions for the examination`
  line `of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) the Authority or the Registrar may, subject to any rule made in this behalf under this Act,`
  line `make such orders as to cost as it considers reasonable and any such order shall be executable as a`
  line `decree of a civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1840)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Registry and offices thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1840&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall establish, for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, a Registry which shall be known as the Plant Varieties Registry.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Plant Varieties Registry shall be located in the head office of the Authority,`
  line `and for the purpose of facilitating the registration of varieties, there may be established, at such places, as`
  line `the Authority may think fit, branch offices of the Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall appoint a Registrar-General of Plant Varieties who shall be entitled to such`
  line `salary and allowances and shall be subject to such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension,`
  line `provident fund and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority may appoint such number of Registrars as it thinks necessary for registration of`
  line `plant varieties under the superintendence and direction of the Registrar-General under this Act and may`
  line `make regulations with respect to their duties and jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office and the conditions of service of the Registrars shall be such as may be provided`
  line `by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority may, by notification in the Official Gazette, define the territorial limits within`
  line `which a branch office of the Registry may exercise its functions.`
  line
  line `(7) There shall be a seal of the Plant Varieties Registry.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1841)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `National Register of Plant Varieties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1841&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, a Register called the`
  line `National Register of Plant Varieties shall be kept at the head office of the Registry, wherein shall be`
  line `entered the names of all the registered plant varieties with the names and addresses of their respective`
  line `breeders, the right of such breeders in respect of the registered varieties, the particulars of the`
  line `denomination of each Registered variety, its seed or other propagating material along with specification`
  line `of salient features thereof and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the superintendence and direction of the Central Government, the Register shall be kept`
  line `under the control and management of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be kept at each branch office of the Registry a copy of the Register and such other`
  line `documents as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1842)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1842&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any person specified in section 16 may make an application to`
  line `the Registrar for registration of any variety--`
  line
  line `(a) of such genera and species as specified under sub-section (2) of section 29; or`
  line
  line `(b) which is an extant variety; or`
  line
  line `(c) which is a farmers' variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1843)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Registrable varieties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1843&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) A new variety shall be registered under this Act if it conforms to the`
  line `criteria of novelty, distinctiveness, uniformity and stability.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an extant variety shall be registered under`
  line `this Act within a specified period if it conforms to such criteria of distinctiveness, uniformity and stability`
  line `as shall be specified under the regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-sections (1) and (2), as the case may be, a new variety shall be deemed to`
  line be--
  line
  line `(a) novel, if, at the date of filing of the application for registration for protection, the propagating`
  line `or harvested material of such variety has not been sold or otherwise disposed of by or with the`
  line `consent of its breeder or his successor for the purposes of exploitation of such variety--`
  line
  line `(i) in India, earlier than one year; or`
  line
  line `(ii) outside India, in the case of trees or vines earlier than six years, or in any other case,`
  line `earlier than four years,`
  line `before the date of filing such application:`
  line
  line `Provided that a trial of a new variety which has not been sold or otherwise disposed of shall not`
  line `affect the right to protection:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the fact that on the date of filing the application for registration, the`
  line `propagating or harvested material of such variety has become a matter of common knowledge other`
  line `than through the aforesaid manner shall not affect the criteria of novelty for such variety;`
  line
  line `(b) distinct, if it is clearly distinguishable by at least one essential characteristic from any another`
  line `variety whose existence is a matter of common knowledge in any country at the time of filing of the`
  line application.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the filing of an application for`
  line `the granting of a breeders right to a new variety or for entering such variety in the official register of`
  line `varieties in any convention country shall be deemed to render that variety a matter of common`
  line `knowledge from the date of the application in case the application leads to the granting of the`
  line `breeder's right or to the entry of such variety in such official register, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) uniform, if subject to the variation that may be expected from the particular features of its`
  line `propagation it is sufficiently uniform in its essential characteristics;`
  line
  line `(d) stable, if its essential characteristics remain unchanged after repeated propagation or, in the`
  line `case of a particular cycle of propagation, at the end of each such cycle.`
  line
  line `(4) A new variety shall not be registered under this Act if the denomination given to such variety--`
  line
  line `(i) is not capable of identifying such variety; or`
  line
  line `(ii) consists solely of figures; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is liable to mislead or to cause confusion concerning the characteristics, value identity of`
  line `such variety or the identity of breeder of such variety; or`
  line
  line `(iv) is not different from every denomination which designates a variety of the same botanical`
  line `species or of a closely related species registered under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(v) is likely to deceive the public or cause confusion in the public regarding the identity of`
  line `such variety; or`
  line
  line `(vi) is likely to hurt the religious sentiments respectively of any class or section of the citizens`
  line `of India; or`
  line
  line `(vii) is prohibited for use as a name or emblem for any of the purposes mentioned in`
  line `section 3 of the Emblems and Names (Prevention of Improper Use) Act, 1950 (12 of 1950); or`
  line
  line `(viii) is comprised of solely or partly of geographical name:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registrar may register a variety, the denomination of which comprises solely or`
  line `partly of a geographical name, if he considers that the use of such denomination in respect of such variety`
  line `is an honest use under the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1844)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Persons who may make application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1844&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for registration under section 14 shall`
  line `be made by--`
  line
  line `(a) any person claiming to be the breeder of the variety; or`
  line
  line `(b) any successor of the breeder of the variety; or`
  line
  line `(c) any person being the assignee of the breeder of the variety in respect of the right to make such`
  line `application; or`
  line
  line `(d) any farmer or group of farmers or community of farmers claiming to be the breeder of the`
  line `variety; or`
  line
  line `(e) any person authorised in the prescribed manner by a person specified under clauses (a) to (d)`
  line `to make application on his behalf; or`
  line
  line `(f) any university or publicly funded agricultural institution claiming to be the breeder of the`
  line variety.
  line
  line `(2) An application under sub-section (1) may be made by any of the persons referred to therein`
  line `individually or jointly with any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1845)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Compulsory variety denomination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1845&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every applicant shall assign a single and distinct`
  line `denomination to a variety with respect to which he is seeking registration under this Act in accordance`
  line `with the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall, having regard to the provisions of any international convention or treaty to`
  line `which India has become a party, make regulations governing the assignment of denomination to a variety.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the denomination assigned to the variety does not satisfy the requirements specified in the`
  line `regulations, the Registrar may require the applicant to propose another denomination within such time as`
  line `may be specified by such regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999), a denomination`
  line `assigned to a variety shall not be registered as a trade mark under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1846)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Form of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1846&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for registration under section 14 shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be with respect to a variety;`
  line
  line `(b) state the denomination assigned to such variety by the applicant;`
  line
  line `(c) be accompanied by an affidavit sworn by the applicant that such variety does not contain any`
  line `gene or gene sequence involving terminator technology;`
  line
  line `(d) be in such form as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) contain a complete passport data of the parental lines from which the variety has been derived`
  line `along with the geographical location in India from where the genetic material has been taken and all`
  line `such information relating to the contribution, if any, of any farmer, village community, institution or`
  line `organisation in breeding, evolving or developing the variety;`
  line
  line `(f) be accompanied by a statement containing a brief description of the variety bringing out its`
  line `characteristics of novelty, distinctiveness, uniformity and stability as required for registration;`
  line
  line `(g) be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(h) contain a declaration that the genetic material or parental material acquired for breeding,`
  line `evolving or developing the variety has been lawfully acquired; and`
  line
  line `(i) be accompanied by such other particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case where the application is for the registration of farmers' variety, nothing`
  line `contained in clauses (b) to (i) shall apply in respect of the application and the application shall be in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application referred to in sub-section (1) shall be filed in the office of the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(3) Where such application is made by virtue of a succession or an assignment of the right to apply`
  line `for registration, there shall be furnished at the time of making the application, or within such period after`
  line `making the application as may be prescribed, a proof of the right to make the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1847)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Test to be conducted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1847&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every applicant shall, along with the application for registration`
  line `made under this Act, make available to the Registrar such quantity of seed of a variety for registration of`
  line `which such application is made, for the purpose of conducting tests to evaluate whether seed of such`
  line `variety along with parental material conform to the standards as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar or any person or test centre to whom such seed has been sent for`
  line `conducting test shall keep such seed during his or its possession in such manner and in such condition that`
  line `its viability and quality shall remain unaltered.`
  line
  line `(2) The applicant shall deposit such fees as may be prescribed for conducting tests referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The tests referred to in sub-section (1) shall be conducted in such manner and by such method as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1848)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Acceptance of application or amendment thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1848&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application under`
  line `section 14, the Registrar may, after making such inquiry as he thinks fit with respect to the particulars`
  line `contained in such application, accept the application absolutely or subject to such conditions or`
  line `limitations as he deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Registrar is satisfied that the application does not comply with the requirements of this`
  line `Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder, he may, either--`
  line
  line `(a) require the applicant to amend the application to his satisfaction; or`
  line
  line `(b) reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of presenting his case.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1849)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Advertisement of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1849&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application for registration of a variety has been`
  line `accepted absolutely or subject to conditions or limitations under sub-section (1) of section 20, the`
  line `Registrar shall, as soon as after its acceptance, cause such application together with the conditions or`
  line `limitations, if any, subject to which it has been accepted and the specifications of the variety for`
  line `registration of which such application is made including its photographs or drawings, to be advertised in`
  line `the prescribed manner calling objections from the persons interested in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person may, within three months from the date of the advertisement of an application for`
  line `registration on payment of the prescribed fees, give notice in writing in the prescribed manner, to the`
  line `Registrar of his opposition to the registration.`
  line
  line `(3) Opposition to the registration under sub-section (2) may be made on any of the following grounds,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the person opposing the application is entitled to the breeders right as against the`
  line `applicant; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the variety is not registrable under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the grant of certificate of registration may not be in public interest; or`
  line
  line `(d) that the variety may have adverse effect on the environment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall serve a copy of the notice of opposition on the applicant for registration and,`
  line `within two months from the receipt by the applicant of such copy of the notice of opposition, the`
  line `applicant shall send to the Registrar in the prescribed manner a counter-statement of the grounds on which`
  line `he relies for his application, and if he does not do so, he shall be deemed to have abandoned his`
  line application
  line
  line `(5) If the applicant sends such counter-statement, the Registrar shall serve a copy thereof on the`
  line `person giving notice of opposition.`
  line
  line `(6) Any evidence upon which the opponent and the applicant may rely shall be submitted, in the`
  line `manner prescribed and within the time prescribed, to the Registrar and the Registrar shall give an`
  line `opportunity to them to be heard, if so desired.`
  line
  line `(7) The Registrar shall, after hearing the parties, if so required, and considering the evidence, decide`
  line `whether and subject to what conditions or limitations, if any, the registration is to be permitted and may`
  line `take into account a ground of objection whether relied upon by the opponent or not.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a person giving notice of opposition or an applicant sending a counter-statement after`
  line `receipt of a copy of such notice neither resides nor carries on business in India, the Registrar may require`
  line `him to give security for the cost of proceedings before him and in default of such security being duly`
  line `given may treat the opposition or application, as the case may be, as abandoned.`
  line
  line `(9) The Registrar may, on request, permit correction of any error in, or any amendment of, a notice of`
  line `opposition or a counter-statement on such terms as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1850)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Registrar to consider grounds of opposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1850&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar shall consider all the grounds on`
  line `which the application has been opposed and after giving reasons for his decision, by order, uphold or`
  line `reject the opposition.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1851)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Registration of essentially derived variety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1851&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for the registration of an`
  line `essentially derived variety of the genera or species specified under sub-section (2) of section 29 by the`
  line `Central Government shall be made to the Registrar by or on behalf of any person referred to in section 14`
  line `and in the manner specified in section 18 as if for the word variety, the words essentially derived`
  line `variety have been substituted therein and shall be accompanied by such documents and fees as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) When the Registrar is satisfied that the requirements of sub-section (1) have been complied with`
  line `to his satisfaction, he shall forward the application with his report and all the relevant document to the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (2), the Authority shall get examined such`
  line `essentially derived variety to determine as to whether the essentially derived variety is a variety derived`
  line `from the initial variety by conducting such tests and following such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) When the Authority is satisfied on the report of the test referred to in sub-section (3) that the`
  line `essentially derived variety has been derived from the initial variety, it may direct the Registrar to register`
  line `such essentially derived variety and the Registrar shall comply with the direction of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Authority is not satisfied on the report of the test referred to in sub-section (3) that the`
  line `essentially derived variety has been derived from the initial variety it shall refuse the application.`
  line
  line `(6) The rights of the breeder of a variety contained in section 28 shall apply to the breeder of`
  line `essentially derived variety:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authorisation by the breeder of the initial variety to the breeder of essentially derived`
  line `variety under sub-section (2) of section 28 may be subject to such terms and conditions as both the parties`
  line `may mutually agree upon.`
  line
  line `(7) An essentially derived variety shall not be registered under this section unless it satisfies the`
  line `requirements of section 15 as if for the word variety, the words essentially derived variety have been`
  line `substituted therein.`
  line
  line `(8) When an essentially derived variety has been registered by the Registrar in compliance with the`
  line `direction of the Authority under sub-section (4), the Registrar shall issue to the applicant a certificate of`
  line `registration in the prescribed form and sealed with the seal of the Registry and send a copy thereof to the`
  line `Authority and to such other authority, as may be prescribed, for information.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1852)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Issue of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1852&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application for registration of a variety (other`
  line `than an essentially derived variety) has been accepted and either--`
  line
  line `(a) the application has not been opposed and the time of notice of opposition has expired; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has been opposed and the opposition has been rejected,`
  line
  line `the Registrar shall register the variety.`
  line
  line `(2) On the registration of the variety (other than an essentially derived variety), the Registrar shall`
  line `issue to the applicant a certificate of registration in the prescribed form and sealed with the seal of the`
  line `Registry and send a copy thereof to the Authority for determination of benefit sharing and to such other authority,`
  line `as may be prescribed, for information. The maximum time required by the Registrar for issuing the`
  line `certificate of registration from the date of filing of the application for registration of a variety shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where registration of a variety (other than an essentially derived variety), is not completed within`
  line `twelve months from the date of the application by reason of default on the part of the applicant, the`
  line `Registrar may, after giving notice to the applicant in the prescribed manner, treat the application as`
  line `abandoned unless it is completed within the time specified in that behalf in the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar may amend the register or a certificate of registration for the purpose of correcting a`
  line `clerical error or an obvious mistake.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar shall have power to issue such directions to protect the interests of a breeder against`
  line `any abusive act committed by any third party during the period between filing of application for`
  line `registration and decision taken by the Authority on such application.`
  line
  line `(6) The certificate of registration issued under this section or sub-section (8) of section 23 shall be`
  line `valid for nine years in the case of trees and vines and six years in the case of other crops and may be`
  line `reviewed and renewed for the remaining period on payment of such fees as may be fixed by the rules made in`
  line `this behalf subject to the condition that the total period of validity shall not exceed,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of trees and vines, eighteen years from the date of registration of the variety;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of extant variety, fifteen years from the date of the notification of that variety by`
  line `the Central Government under section 5 of the Seeds Act, 1966 (54 of 1966); and`
  line
  line `(iii) in other cases, fifteen years from the date of registration of the variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1853)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Publication of list of varieties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1853&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall, within such intervals as it thinks`
  line `appropriate, publish the list of varieties which have been registered during that interval.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1854)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Determination of benefit sharing by Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1854&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of copy of the certificate of`
  line `registration under sub-section (8) of section 23 or sub-section (2) of section 24, the Authority shall`
  line `publish such contents of the certificate and invite claims of benefit sharing to the variety registered under`
  line `such certificate in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) On invitation of the claims under sub-section (1), any person or group of persons or firm or`
  line `governmental or non-governmental organisation shall submit its claim of benefit sharing to such variety`
  line `in the prescribed form within such period, and accompanied with such fees, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such claim shall only be submitted by any--`
  line
  line `(i) person or group of persons, if such person or every person constituting such group is a citizen`
  line `of India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) firm or governmental or non-governmental organisation, if such firm or organisation is`
  line `formed or established in India.`
  line
  line `(3) On receiving a claim under sub-section (2), the Authority shall send a copy of such claim to the`
  line `breeder of the variety registered under such certificate and the breeder may, on receipt of such copy,`
  line `submit his opposition to such claim within such period and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the parties, dispose of the claim`
  line `received under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) While disposing of the claim under sub-section (4), the Authority shall explicitly indicate in its`
  line `order the amount of the benefit sharing, if any, for which the claimant shall be entitled and shall take into`
  line `consideration the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the extent and nature of the use of genetic material of the claimant in the development of the`
  line `variety relating to which the benefit sharing has been claimed;`
  line
  line `(b) the commercial utility and demand in the market of the variety relating to which the benefit`
  line `sharing has been claimed.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of benefit sharing to a variety determined under this section shall be deposited by the`
  line `breeder of such variety in the manner referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 45 in the`
  line `National Gene Fund.`
  line
  line `(7) The amount of benefit sharing determined under this section shall, on a reference made by the`
  line `Authority in the prescribed manner, be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue by the District Magistrate`
  line `within whose local limits of jurisdiction the breeder liable for such benefit sharing resides.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1855)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Breeder to deposit seeds or propagating material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1855&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The breeder shall be required to deposit`
  line `such quantity of seeds or propagating material including parental line seeds of registered variety in the`
  line `National Gene Bank as may be specified in the regulations for reproduction purpose at the breeder's`
  line `expense within such time as may be specified in that regulation.`
  line
  line `(2) The seeds or propagating material or parental line seeds to be deposited under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be deposited to the National Gene Bank specified by the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1856)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Registration to confer right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1856&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, a certificate of`
  line `registration for a variety issued under this Act shall confer an exclusive right on the breeder or his`
  line `successor, his agent or licensee, to produce, sell, market, distribute, import or export the variety:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an extant variety, unless a breeder or his successor establishes his right,`
  line `the Central Government, and in cases where such extant variety is notified for a State or for any area`
  line `thereof under section 5 of the Seeds Act, 1966 (54 of 1966), the State Government, shall be deemed to be`
  line `the owner of such right.`
  line
  line `(2) A breeder may authorise any person to produce, sell, market or otherwise deal with the variety`
  line `registered under this Act subject to such limitations and conditions as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Every authorisation under this section shall be in such form as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an agent or a licensee referred to in sub-section (1) becomes entitled to produce, sell,`
  line `market, distribute, import or export a variety, he shall apply in the prescribed manner and with the`
  line `prescribed fees to the Registrar to register his title and the Registrar shall, on receipt of application and on`
  line `proof of title to his satisfaction, register him as an agent or a licensee, as the case may be, in respect of the`
  line `variety for which he is entitled for such right, and shall cause particulars of such entitlement and`
  line `conditions or restrictions, if any, subject to which such entitlement is made, to be entered in the Register:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the validity of such entitlement is in dispute between the parties, the Registrar`
  line `may refuse to register the entitlement and refer the matter in the prescribed manner to the Authority and`
  line `withhold the registration of such entitlement until the right of the parties in dispute so referred to has been`
  line `determined by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar shall issue a certificate of registration under sub-section (4) to the applicant after`
  line `such registration and shall enter in the certificate the brief conditions of entitlement, if any, in the`
  line `prescribed manner, and such certificate shall be the conclusive proof of such entitlement and the`
  line `conditions or restrictions thereof, if any.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to any agreement subsisting between the parties, an agent or licensee of a right to a variety`
  line `registered under sub-section (4) shall be entitled to call upon the breeder or his successor thereof to take`
  line `proceedings to prevent infringement thereof, and if the breeder or his successor refuses or neglects to do`
  line `so within three months after being so called upon, such registered agent or licensee may institute`
  line `proceedings for infringement in his own name as if he were the breeder, making the breeder or his`
  line `successor a defendant.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, a breeder or his successor so added as`
  line `defendant shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceedings.
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in this section shall confer on a registered agent or registered licensee of a variety any`
  line `right to transfer such right further thereof.`
  line
  line `(9) Without prejudice to the registration under sub-section (4), the terms of registration`
  line
  line `(a) may be varied by the Registrar as regards the variety in respect of which, or any condition or`
  line `restriction subject to which, it has effect on receipt of an application in the prescribed manner of the`
  line `registered breeder of such variety or his successor;`
  line
  line `(b) may be cancelled by the Registrar on the application in the prescribed manner of the`
  line `registered breeder of such variety or his successor or of the registered agent or registered licensee of`
  line `such variety;`
  line
  line `(c) may be cancelled by the Registrar on the application in the prescribed manner of any person`
  line `other than the breeder, his successor, the registered agent or the registered licensee on any of the`
  line `following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the breeder of a variety or his successor or the registered agent or registered licensee`
  line `of such variety, misrepresented, or failed to disclose, some fact material to the application for`
  line `registration under sub-section (4) which if accurately represented or disclosed would have`
  line `justified the refusal of the application for registration of the registered agent or registered`
  line licensee;
  line
  line `(ii) that the registration ought not to have been effected having regard to the right vested in the`
  line `applicant by virtue of a contract in the performance of which he is interested;`
  line
  line `(d) may be cancelled by the Registrar on the application in the prescribed manner of the breeder`
  line `of a registered variety or his successor on the ground that any stipulation in the agreement between`
  line `the registered agent or the registered licensee, as the case may be, and such breeder or his successor`
  line `regarding the variety for which such agent or licensee is registered is not being enforced or is not`
  line `being complied with;`
  line
  line `(e) may be cancelled by the registrar on the application of any person in the prescribed manner on`
  line `the ground that the variety relating to the registration is no longer existing.`
  line
  line `(10) The registrar shall issue notice in the prescribed manner of' every application under this section`
  line `to the registered breeder of a variety or his successor and to each registered agent or registered licensee`
  line `(not being the applicant) of such variety.`
  line
  line `(11) The Registrar shall, before making any order under sub-section (9), forward the application made`
  line `in that behalf along with any objection received by any party after notice under sub-section (10) for the`
  line `consideration of the Authority, and the Authority may, after making such inquiry as it thinks fit, issue`
  line `such directions to the Registrar as it thinks fit and the Registrar shall dispose of the application in`
  line `accordance with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1857)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Exclusion of certain varieties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1857&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no`
  line `registration of a variety shall be made under this Act in cases where prevention of commercial`
  line `exploitation of such variety is necessary to protect public order or public morality or human, animal and`
  line `plant life and health or to avoid serious prejudice to the environment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the genera or`
  line `species for the purposes of registration of varieties other than extant varieties and farmers varieties under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained under sub-section (2) and sub-sections (1) and (2)`
  line `of section 15, no variety of any genera or species which involves any technology which is injurious to the`
  line `life or health of human beings, animals or plants shall be registered under this Act.`
  line
  line .
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "any technology" includes genetic`
  line `use restriction technology and terminator technology.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall not delete any genera or species from the list of genera or species`
  line `specified in a notification issued under sub-section (2) except in the public interest.`
  line
  line `(5) Any variety belonging to the genera or species excluded under sub-section (4) shall not be eligible`
  line `for any protection under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1858)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Researcher’s rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1858&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall prevent--`
  line
  line `(a) the use of any variety registered under this Act by any person using such variety for`
  line `conducting experiment or research; or`
  line
  line `(b) the use of a variety by any person as an initial source of variety for the purpose of creating`
  line `other varieties:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authorisation of the breeder of a registered variety is required where the repeated`
  line `use of such variety as a parental line is necessary for commercial production of such other newly`
  line `developed variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1859)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Special provisions relating to application for registration from citizens of convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1859&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to the fulfilment of a treaty, convention or arrangement with any country`
  line `outside India which affords to citizens of India similar privileges as granted to its own citizens, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such country to be a convention`
  line `country for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person has made an application for the granting of a breeder's right to a variety or for`
  line `entering such variety in the official register of varieties in a convention country and that person, or any`
  line `person entitled to make application on his behalf under section 14 or section 23, makes an application for`
  line `the registration of such variety in India within twelve months after the date on which the application was`
  line `made in the convention country, such variety shall, if registered under this Act, be registered as of the`
  line `date on which the application was made in the convention country and that date shall be deemed for the`
  line `purposes of this Act to be the date of registration.`
  line
  line `(3) Where applications have been made for granting of a breeder's right to a variety, or for entering`
  line `such variety in the official register of varieties in two or more convention countries, the period of twelve`
  line `months referred to in sub-section (2) shall be reckoned from the date on which the earlier or earliest of`
  line `those applications were made.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this Act shall entitle the breeder of a registered variety for infringement of rights other`
  line `than protected under this Act which took place prior to the date of application of registration under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1860)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Provisions as to reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1860&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Where any country declared by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf by notification in the Official Gazette under sub-section (1) of section 31 does not accord to`
  line `citizens of India the same rights in respect of the registration and protection of a variety, as it accords to`
  line `its own nationals, no national of such country shall be entitled, either solely or jointly with any other`
  line `person, to apply for the registration of a variety or be entitled to get a variety registered under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1861)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Surrender of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1861&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A breeder of a variety registered under this Act`
  line `may, at any time by giving notice in the prescribed manner to the Registrar, offer to surrender his`
  line `certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such an offer is made, the Registrar shall notify in the prescribed manner every registered`
  line `agent or registered licensee relating to such certificate.`
  line
  line `(3) Any of such agent or licensee may, within the prescribed period after such notification, give`
  line `notice to the Registrar of his opposition to the surrender and where any such notice is given, the Registrar`
  line `shall intimate the contents of such notice to the breeder of such variety.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Registrar is satisfied after hearing the applicant and all the opponents, if desirous of being`
  line `heard, that the certificate of registration may properly be surrendered, he may accept the offer and by`
  line `order revoke the certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (1862)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Revocation of protection on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1862&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in this Act,`
  line `the protection granted to a breeder in respect of a variety may, on the application in the prescribed manner`
  line `of any person interested, be revoked by the Authority on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the grant of the certificate of registration has been based on incorrect information`
  line `furnished by the applicant;`
  line
  line `(b) that the certificate of registration has been granted to a person who is not eligible for`
  line `protection under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) that the breeder did not provide the Registrar with such information, documents or material as`
  line `required for registration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) that the breeder has failed to provide an alternative denomination of the variety which is the`
  line `subject matter of the registration to the Registrar in case where the earlier denomination of such`
  line `variety provided to the Registrar is not permissible for registration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) that the breeder did not provide the necessary seeds or propagating material to the person to`
  line `whom compulsory licence has been issued under section 47 regarding the variety in respect of which`
  line `registration certificate has been issued to such breeder;`
  line
  line `(f) that the breeder has not complied with the provisions of this Act or rules or regulations made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(g) that the breeder has failed to comply with the directions of the Authority issued under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(h) that the grant of the certificate of registration is not in the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such protection shall be revoked unless the breeder is given a reasonable opportunity`
  line `to file objection and of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1863)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Payment of annual fees and forfeiture of registration in default thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1863&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority`
  line `may, with the prior approval of the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, impose a`
  line `fee to be paid annually, by every breeder of a variety, agent and licensee thereof registered under this Act`
  line `determined on the basis of benefit or royalty gained by such breeder, agent or licensee, as the case may`
  line `be, in respect of the variety, for the retention of their registration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If any breeder, agent or licensee fails to deposit the fees referred to in sub-section (1) imposed`
  line `upon him under that sub-section in the prescribed manner up to two consecutive years, the Authority shall`
  line `issue notice to such breeder, agent or licensee and on service of such notice if he fails to comply with the`
  line `direction in the notice, the Authority shall declare all the protection admissible under the registration`
  line `certificate issued to such breeder or agent or licensee forfeited.`
  line
  line `(3) The arrears of fee imposed under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be the arrears of land revenue`
  line `and shall be recoverable accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1864)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to cancel or change registration and to rectify the Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1864&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) On an application`
  line `made in the prescribed manner to the Registrar by any person aggrieved, the Registrar may make such`
  line `order as he may think fit for cancelling or changing any certificate of registration issued under this Act on`
  line `the ground of any contravention of the provisions of this Act or failure to observe a condition subject to`
  line `which such registration certificate is issued.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by the absence or omission from the Register of any entry, or by any entry`
  line `made in the Register without sufficient cause, or by any entry wrongly remaining on the Register, may`
  line `apply in the prescribed manner to the Registrar and the Registrar may make such order for making,`
  line `expunging or varying the entry as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar may, in any proceeding under this section, decide any question that may be`
  line `necessary or expedient to decide in connection with the rectification of the Register.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar on his own motion may, after giving notice in the prescribed manner to the parties`
  line `concerned and after giving them an opportunity of being heard, make any order referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1865)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Correction of Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1865&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar may, on an application in the prescribed manner by`
  line `the breeder of a variety registered under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any error in the Register in the name, address or description of such breeder or any`
  line `other entry relating to such variety;`
  line
  line `(b) enter in the Register any change in the name, address or description of such breeder;`
  line
  line `(c) cancel the entry in the Register of the variety in respect of which such application is made;`
  line `and may make any consequential amendment or alteration in the certificate of registration and for`
  line `that purpose require the certificate of registration to be produced to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may, on application made in the prescribed manner by a registered agent or a`
  line `registered licensee of a variety and after notice to the registered breeder of such variety, correct any error,`
  line `or enter any change, in the name, address or description of such registered agent or registered licensee, as`
  line `the case may be, in the Register or certificate of registration issued under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1866)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Alteration of denomination of a registered variety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1866&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The breeder of a variety registered`
  line `under this Act may apply in the prescribed manner to the Registrar to delete any part or to add to or alter`
  line `the denomination of such variety in any manner not substantially affecting the identity thereof, and the`
  line `Registrar may refuse leave or may grant it on such terms and subject to such limitations as he may think`
  line `fit to avoid any conflict with the rights of other breeders of the varieties registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may cause an application under this section to be advertised in the prescribed`
  line `manner in any case where it appears to him that it is expedient so to do, and where he does so, if within`
  line `the prescribed time from the date of the advertisement any person gives notice to the Registrar in the`
  line `prescribed manner of opposition to the application, the Registrar shall, after hearing the parties if so`
  line `required, decide the matter.`
  line
  line `(3) Where leave is granted under this section, the denomination of the variety as altered shall be`
  line `advertised in the prescribed manner, unless the application has already been advertised under`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (1867)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Farmers’ rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1867&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,-`
  line
  line `(i) a farmer who has bred or developed a new variety shall be entitled for registration and other`
  line `protection in like manner as a breeder of a variety under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the farmers' variety shall be entitled for registration if the application contains declarations as`
  line `specified in clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(iii) a farmer who is engaged in the conservation of genetic resources of land races and wild`
  line `relatives of economic plants and their improvement through selection and preservation shall be`
  line `entitled in the prescribed manner for recognition and reward from the Gene Fund:`
  line
  line `Provided that material so selected and preserved has been used as donors of genes in varieties`
  line `registrable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iv) a farmer shall be deemed to be entitled to save, use, sow resow, exchange, share or sell his`
  line `farm produce including seed of a variety protected under this Act in the same manner as he was`
  line `entitled before the coming into force of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the farmer shall not be entitled to sell branded seed of a variety protected under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of clause (iv), "branded seed" means any seed put in a package or any`
  line `other container and labelled in a manner indicating that such seed is of a variety protected under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any propagating material of a variety registered under this Act has been sold to a farmer or`
  line `a group of farmers or any organisation of farmers, the breeder of such variety shall disclose to the farmer`
  line `or the group of farmers or the organisation of farmers, as the case may be, the expected performance`
  line `under given conditions, and if such propagating material fails to provide such performance under such`
  line `given conditions, the farmer or the group of farmers or the organisation of farmers, the case may be, may`
  line `claim compensation in the prescribed manner before the Authority and the Authority, after giving notice`
  line `to the breeder of the variety and after providing him an opportunity to file opposition in the prescribed`
  line `manner and after hearing the parties, may direct the breeder of the variety to pay such compensation as it`
  line `deems fit, to the farmer or the group of farmers or the organisation of farmers, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (1868)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Certain information to be given in application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1868&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) A breeder or other person`
  line `making application for registration of any variety under Chapter III shall disclose in the application the`
  line `information regarding the use of genetic material conserved by any tribal or rural families in the breeding`
  line `or development of such variety.`
  line
  line `(2) If the breeder or such other person fails to disclose any information under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Registrar may, after being satisfied that the breeder or such person has wilfully and knowingly concealed`
  line `such information, reject the application for registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (1869)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Rights of communities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1869&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person or group of persons (whether actively engaged in`
  line `farming or not) or any governmental or non-governmental organisation may, on behalf of any village or`
  line `local community in India, file in any centre notified, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by the Authority, in the Official Gazette, any claim attributable to the contribution of the`
  line `people of that village or local community, as the case may be, in the evolution of any variety for the`
  line `purpose of staking a claim on behalf of such village or local community.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any claim is made under sub-section (1), the centre notified under that sub-section may`
  line `verify the claim made by such person or group of persons or such governmental or non-governmental`
  line `organisation in such manner as it deems fit, and if it is satisfied that such village or local community has`
  line `contributed significantly to the evolution of the variety which has been registered under this Act, it shall`
  line `report its findings to the Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) When the Authority, on a report under sub-section (2) is satisfied, after such inquiry as it may`
  line `deem fit, that the variety with which the report is related has been registered under the provisions of this`
  line `Act, it may issue notice in the prescribed manner to the breeder of that variety and after providing`
  line `opportunity to such breeder to file objection in the prescribed manner and of being heard, it may subject`
  line `to any limit notified by the Central Government, by order, grant such sum of compensation to be paid to a`
  line `person or group of persons or governmental or non-governmental organisation which has made claim`
  line `under sub-section (1), as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Any compensation granted under sub-section (3) shall be deposited by the breeder of the variety`
  line `in the Gene Fund.`
  line
  line `(5) The compensation granted under sub-section (3) shall be deemed to be an arrear of land revenue`
  line `and shall be recoverable by the Authority accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (1870)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Protection of innocent infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1870&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) a right established under this Act shall not be deemed to be infringed by a farmer who at the`
  line `time of such infringement was not aware of the existence of such right; and`
  line
  line `(ii) a relief which a court may grant in any suit for infringement referred to in section 65 shall not`
  line `be granted by such court, nor any cognizance of any offence under this Act shall be taken, for such`
  line `infringement by any court against a farmer who proves, before such court, that at the time of the`
  line `infringement he was not aware of the existence of the right so infringed.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (1871)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Authorisation of farmers’ variety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1871&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 23 and section 28, where an essentially derived variety is derived from a farmers' variety, the`
  line `authorisation under sub-section (2) of section 28 shall not be given by the breeder of such farmers variety`
  line `except with the consent of the farmers or group of farmers or community of farmers who have made`
  line `contribution in the preservation or development of such variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (1872)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Exemption from fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. The words “or the Tribunal” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1872&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `A farmer or group of farmers or village community shall not be liable to`
  line `pay any fees in any proceeding before the Authority or Registrar ^1***or the High Court under`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, fees in any proceeding includes any fees payable`
  line `for inspection of any document or for obtaining a copy of any decision or order or document under this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (1873)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Gene Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1873&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a Fund to be called the National Gene`
  line `Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) the benefit sharing received in the prescribed manner from the breeder of a variety or`
  line `an essentially derived variety registered under this Act, or propagating material of such variety or`
  line `essentially derived variety, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) the annual fee payable to the Authority by way of royalty under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(c) the compensation deposited in the Gene Fund under sub-section (4) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(d) the contribution from any national and international organisation and other sources.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gene Fund shall, in the prescribed manner, be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) any amount to be paid by way of benefit sharing under sub-section (5) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(b) the compensation payable under sub-section (3) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(c) the expenditure for supporting the conservation and sustainable use of genetic resources`
  line `including in-situ and ex-situ collections and for strengthening the capability of the Panchayat in`
  line `carrying out such conservation and sustainable use;`
  line
  line `(d) the expenditure of the schemes relating to benefit sharing framed under section 46.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (1874)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Framing of schemes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1874&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the purposes of section 41 and`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 45, frame, by notification in the Official Gazette, one or more`
  line schemes.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `scheme may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the registration of the claims for the purposes of section 41 under the scheme and all matters`
  line `connected with such registration;`
  line
  line `(b) the processing of such claims for securing their enforcement and matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) the maintenance of records and Registers in respect of such claims;`
  line
  line `(d) the utilisation, by way of disbursal (including apportionment) or otherwise, of any amounts`
  line `received in satisfaction of such claims;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure for disbursal or apportionment by the Authority in the event of dispute`
  line `regarding such claims;`
  line
  line `(f) the utilisation of benefit sharing for the purposes relating to breeding, discovery or`
  line `development of varieties;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance and audit of accounts with respect to the amounts referred to in clause (d).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (1875)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of Authority to make order for compulsory licence in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1875&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) At`
  line `any time, after the expiry of three years from the date of issue of a certificate of registration of a variety,`
  line `any person interested may make an application to the Authority alleging that the reasonable requirements`
  line `of the public for seed or other propagating material of the variety have not been satisfied or that the seed`
  line `or other propagating material of the variety is not available to the public at a reasonable price and pray for`
  line `the grant of a compulsory licence to undertake production, distribution and sale of the seed or other`
  line `propagating material of that variety.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall contain a statement of the nature of the applicants`
  line `interest together with such particulars as may be prescribed and the facts upon which the application is`
  line based.
  line
  line `(3) The Authority, after consultation with the Central Government, and if satisfied after giving an`
  line `opportunity to the breeder of such variety to file opposition and after hearing the parties, on the issue that`
  line `the reasonable requirements of the public with respect to the variety have not been satisfied or that the`
  line `seed or other propagating material of the variety is not available to the public at a reasonable price, may`
  line `order such breeder to grant a licence to the applicant upon such terms and conditions as it may deem fit`
  line `and send a copy of such order to the Registrar to register the title of such applicant as licensee under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 28 on payment of such fees by the applicant as is referred to in that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (1876)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `When requirement of public deemed to have not been satisfied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1876&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `In determining the question`
  line `as to whether the reasonable requirements of the public for seeds of a variety or its propagating material`
  line `as referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) of section 47, the Authority shall take into account--`
  line
  line `(i) the nature of the variety, the time which has elapsed since the grant of the certificate of`
  line `registration of the variety, price of the seed of the variety and the measures taken by the breeder or`
  line `any registered licensee of the variety to meet the requirement of the public; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the capacity, ability and technical competence of the applicant to produce and market the`
  line `variety to meet the requirement of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (1877)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Adjournment of application for grant of compulsory licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1877&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the breeder of a variety`
  line `registered under this Act in respect of which any application has been pending before the Authority under`
  line `section 47 makes a written request to the Authority on the ground that due to any reasonable factor, such`
  line `breeder has been unable to produce seed or other propagating material of the variety on a commercial`
  line `scale to an adequate extent till the date of making such request, the Authority may, on being satisfied that`
  line `the said ground is reasonable, adjourn the hearing of such application for such period not exceeding`
  line `twelve months in aggregate as it may consider sufficient for optimum production of the seed or`
  line `propagating material of such variety, as the case may be, by such breeder.`
  line
  line `(2) No adjournment of the application under sub-section (1) shall be granted unless the Authority is`
  line `satisfied that the breeder of the variety registered under this Act in respect of which such application is`
  line `made, has taken immediate measures to meet the reasonable requirements of the public for the seed or`
  line `other propagating material of such variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (1878)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Duration of compulsory licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1878&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall determine the duration of the compulsory`
  line `licences granted under this Chapter and such duration may vary from case to case keeping in view the`
  line `gestation periods and other relevant factors but in any case it shall not exceed the total remaining period of the protection of that variety and when a compulsory licence is granted the prescribed authority shall,`
  line `in the prescribed manner make available to the licensee of such compulsory licence, the reproductive`
  line `material of the variety relating to such compulsory licence stored in the National Gene Bank or any other`
  line centre.
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (1879)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Authority to settle terms and conditions of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1879&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall, while`
  line `determining the terms and conditions of a compulsory licence under the provisions of this Chapter,`
  line `endeavour to secure--`
  line
  line `(i) reasonable compensation to the breeder of the variety relating to the compulsory licence`
  line `having regard to the nature of the variety, the expenditure incurred by such breeder in breeding the`
  line `variety or for developing it, and other relevant factors;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the compulsory licensee of such variety possesses the adequate means to provide to the`
  line `farmers, the seeds or other propagating material of such variety timely and at reasonable market`
  line price.
  line
  line `(2) No compulsory licence granted by the Authority shall authorise the licensee to import the variety`
  line `relating to such licence or any seed or other propagating material of such variety from abroad where such`
  line `import would constitute an infringement of the rights of the breeder of such variety.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (1880)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Revocation of compulsory licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1880&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority, on its own motion or on application`
  line `from an aggrieved person made to it in the prescribed form, if it is satisfied that a compulsory licensee`
  line `registered under this Chapter has violated any terms or conditions of his licence or it is not appropriate to`
  line `continue further such licence in public interest, may, after giving such licensee an opportunity to file`
  line `opposition and of being heard, make order to revoke such licence.`
  line
  line `(2) When a licence is revoked under sub-section (1) by an order of the Authority, the Authority shall`
  line `send a copy of such order to the Registrar to rectify the entry or correct the Register relating to such`
  line `revocation and the Registrar shall rectify the entry or correct the Register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (1881)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Modification of compulsory licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1881&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, on its own motion or on application`
  line `from licensee of a compulsory licence, after providing the opportunity of being heard to the breeder of the`
  line `variety registered under this Act relating to such compulsory licence, if it considers, in public interest, so`
  line `to do, modify, by order, such terms and conditions as it thinks fit and send a copy of such order to the`
  line `Registrar to correct the entries and Register according to such modification and the Registrar shall ensure`
  line `such corrections to be made accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (1882)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title Tribunal.
  content `Omitted by the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021 (33 of 2021), s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1882&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (1883)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Composition of Tribunal.`
  content `Omitted by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1883&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (1884)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Appeals to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1884&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall be preferred to the ^1[High Court] within the prescribed`
  line `period from any--`
  line
  line `(a) order or decision of the Authority or Registrar, relating to registration of a variety; or`
  line
  line `(b) order or decision of the Registrar relating to registration as an agent or a licensee of a variety;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) order or decision of the Authority relating to claim for benefit sharing; or`
  line
  line `(d) order or decision of the Authority regarding revocation of compulsory licence or modification`
  line `of compulsory licence; or`
  line
  line `(e) order or decision of the Authority regarding payment of compensation, made under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such appeal shall be preferred by a petition in writing and shall be in such form and shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2*****.
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for Tribunal (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (1885)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Orders of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1885&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[High Court] may, after giving both the parties to the appeal an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[High Court] may, at any time within thirty days from the date of the order, with a view to`
  line `rectifying the mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it under sub-section (1), and`
  line `make such amendment if the mistake is brought to its notice by the appellant or the opposite party.`
  line
  line `(3) In every appeal, the ^1[High court] may, where it is possible, hear and decide such appeal within a`
  line `period of one year from the date of filing of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^1[High Court] shall send a copy of any order passed under this section to the Registrar.`
  line
  line ^2*****
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for Tribunal (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (5) omitted by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (1886)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Procedure of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1886&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Omitted by the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021 (33 of 2021), s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-`
  line `2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (1887)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Transitional provision.`
  content `Omitted by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1887&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (1888)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1888&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The Central government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Authority grants and loans of such sums of money as the`
  line `Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (1889)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Authority Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1889&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the Protection of Plant`
  line `Varieties Authority Account and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) all grants and loans made to the Authority by the Central Government under section 60;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees received by the Authority and the Registrars except the annual fee determined on the`
  line `basis of benefit or royalty under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by the Authority from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Protection of Plant Varieties Authority Account shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the Chairperson, officers and other`
  line `employees of the Authority and allowances, if any, payable to the members;`
  line
  line `(b) the other expenses of the Authority in connection with the discharge of its functions and for`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (1890)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Budget, accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1890&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall prepare a budget, maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records (including the accounts and other relevant records of the Gene Fund)`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Authority shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in his behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (1891)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Financial and administrative powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1891&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall exercise`
  line `such financial and administrative powers over the functions of the Authority as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall have the authority to delegate such of his financial and`
  line `administrative powers as he may think fit to a member or any other officer of the Authority subject to the`
  line `condition that the member or such other officer shall, while exercising such delegated powers, continue to be`
  line `under the direction, control and supervision of the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (1892)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title Infringement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1892&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, a right established under this Act is`
  line `infringed by a person--`
  line
  line `(a) who, not being the breeder of a variety registered under this Act or a registered agent or`
  line `a registered licensee of that variety, sells, exports, imports or produces such variety without the`
  line `permission of its breeder or within the scope of a registered licence or registered agency without`
  line `permission of the registered licensee or registered agent, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) who uses, sells, exports, imports or produces any other variety giving such variety, the`
  line `denomination identical with or deceptively similar to the denomination of a variety registered under`
  line `this Act in such manner as to cause confusion in the mind or general people in identifying such`
  line `variety so registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (1893)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Suit for infringement, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1893&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit--`
  line
  line `(a) for the infringement of a variety registered under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) relating to any right in a variety registered under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be instituted in any court inferior to a District Court having jurisdiction to try the suit.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1), District Court having jurisdiction shall`
  line `mean the District Court within the local limit of whose jurisdiction the cause of action arises.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (1894)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Relief in suits for infringement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1894&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) The relief which a court may grant in any suit for`
  line `infringement referred to in section 65 includes an injunction and at the option of the plaintiff, either`
  line `damages or a share of the profits.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of injunction under sub-section (1) may include an ex parte injunction or any`
  line `interlocutory order for any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) discovery of documents;`
  line
  line `(b) preserving of infringing variety or documents or other evidence which are related to the`
  line `subject-matter of the suit;`
  line
  line `(c) attachment of such property of the defendant which the court deems necessary to recover`
  line `damages, costs or other pecuniary remedies which may be finally awarded to the plaintiff.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (1895)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Opinion of scientific adviser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1895&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the court has to form an opinion upon any question of`
  line `fact or a scientific issue, such court may appoint an independent scientific adviser to suggest it or to`
  line `inquire into and report upon the matter to enable it to from the desired opinion.`
  line
  line `(2) The scientific adviser may be paid such remuneration or expenses as the court may fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (1896)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Prohibition to apply denomination of a registered variety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1896&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than the`
  line `breeder of a variety registered under this Act or a registered licensee or a registered agent thereof shall use`
  line `the denomination of that variety in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be deemed to apply the denomination of a variety registered under this Act who--`
  line
  line `(a) applies it to the variety itself; or`
  line
  line `(b) applies it to any package in or with which the variety is sold, or exposed for sale, or had in`
  line `possession such package for sale or for any purpose of trade or production; or`
  line
  line `(c) places, encloses or annexes the variety which is sold, or exposed for sale, or had in possession`
  line `for sale or for any purpose of trade or production, in or with any package or other thing to which the`
  line `denomination of such variety registered under this Act has been applied; or`
  line
  line `(d) uses the denomination of such variety registered under this Act in any manner reasonably`
  line `likely to lead to the belief that the variety or its propagating material in connection with which it is`
  line `used is designated or described by that denomination; or`
  line
  line `(e) in relation to the variety uses such denomination in any advertisement, invoice, catalogue,`
  line `business letter, business paper, price list or other commercial document and such variety is delivered`
  line `to a person in pursuance of a request or order made by reference to the denomination as so used.`
  line
  line `(3) A denomination shall be deemed to be applied to a variety whether it is woven in, impressed on,`
  line `or otherwise worked into, or annexed or affixed to, such variety or to any package or other thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (1897)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Meaning of falsely applying denomination of a registered variety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1897&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be`
  line `deemed to falsely apply the denomination of a variety registered under this Act who, without the assent of`
  line `the breeder of such variety,--`
  line
  line `(a) applies such denomination or a deceptively similar denomination to any variety or any`
  line `package containing such variety;`
  line
  line `(b) uses any package bearing a denomination which is identical with or deceptively similar to the`
  line `denomination of such variety registered under this Act, for the purpose of packing, filling or wrapping`
  line `therein any variety other than such variety registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any denomination of a variety registered under this Act falsely applied as mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1), is in this Act referred to as false denomination.`
  line
  line `(3) In any prosecution for falsely applying a denomination of a variety registered under this Act the`
  line `burden of proving the assent of the breeder of such variety shall lie on the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (1898)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Penalty for applying false denomination, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1898&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) applies any false denomination to a variety; or`
  line
  line `(b) indicates the false name of a country or place or false name and address of the breeder of a`
  line `variety registered under this Act in the course of trading such variety,`
  line
  line `shall, unless he proves that he acted, without intend to defraud, be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than three months but which may extend to two years, or with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (1899)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Penalty for selling varieties to which false denomination is applied, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1899&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Any person who`
  line `sells, or exposes for sale, or has in his possession for sale or for any purpose of trade or production of any`
  line `variety to which any false denomination is applied or to which an indication of the country or place in which such variety was made or produced or the name and address of the breeder of such variety`
  line `registered under this Act has been falsely made, shall, unless he proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that having taken all reasonable precautions against committing an offence against this`
  line `section, he had at the time of commission of the alleged offence no reason to suspect the genuineness`
  line `of the denomination of such variety or that any offence had been committed in respect of indication of`
  line `the country or place in which such variety registered under this Act, was made or produced or the`
  line `name and address of the breeder of such variety;`
  line
  line `(b) that, on demand by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his`
  line `possession with respect to the person from whom he obtained such variety; or`
  line
  line `(c) that otherwise he had acted innocently,`
  line
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend`
  line `to five lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (1900)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Penalty for falsely representing a variety as registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1900&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes any representation`
  line `with respect to the denomination of a variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety or`
  line `its propagating material not being variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety or its`
  line `propagating material registered under this Act, to the effect that it is a variety or its propagating material`
  line `or essentially derived variety or its propagating material registered under this Act or otherwise represents`
  line `any variety, or its propagating material, or essentially derived variety or its propagating material not`
  line `registered under this Act to the effect that it is registered under this Act shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term, which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (1901)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Penalty for subsequent offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1901&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having already been convicted of an offence under`
  line `this Act is again convicted of such offence shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent`
  line `offence with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to three`
  line `years, or with fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (1902)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `No offence in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1902&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act relating to offences shall be subject to`
  line `the right created as recognised by this Act and no act or omission shall be deemed to be an offence under`
  line `the provisions of this Act if such act or omission is permissible under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (1903)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Exemption of certain persons employed in ordinary course of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1903&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Where a person`
  line `accused of an offence under this Act proves that in the ordinary course of his employment, he has acted`
  line `without any intention to commit the offence and having taken all reasonable precautions against`
  line `committing the offence charged, he had, at the time of the commission of the alleged offence, no reason`
  line `to suspect the genuineness of the act so charged as an offence and on demand made by or on behalf of the`
  line `prosecutor, he gave all the information in his possession with respect to the persons on whose behalf the`
  line `offence was committed, he shall be acquitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (1904)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Procedure where invalidity of registration is pleaded by the accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1904&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the offence`
  line `charged under this Act is in relation to a variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety`
  line `or its propagating material registered under this Act and the accused pleads that the registration of such`
  line `variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety or its propagating material, as the case`
  line `may be, is invalid and the court is satisfied that such offence is prima facie not tenable, it shall not`
  line `proceed with the charge but shall adjourn the proceedings for three months from the date on which the`
  line `plea of the accused is recorded to enable the accused to file an application before the Registrar under this`
  line `Act for the rectification of the Register on the ground that the registration is invalid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused proves to the court that he has made such application within the time so limited or`
  line `within such further time as the court for sufficient cause allow, the further proceedings in the prosecution`
  line `shall stand stayed till the disposal of such application for rectification.`
  line
  line `(3) If within a period of three months or within such extended time as may be allowed by the court,`
  line `the accused fails to apply to the Registrar for rectification of the Register, the court shall proceed with the`
  line `case as if the registration were valid.`
  line
  line `(4) Where before institution of a complaint of an offence referred to in sub-section (1), any`
  line `application for the rectification of the Register concerning the registration of the variety or its propagating`
  line `material or essentially derived variety or its propagating material, as the case may be, in question on the`
  line `ground of invalidity of such registration has already been properly made to and is pending before the`
  line `Registrar, the court shall stay the further proceedings in the prosecution pending the disposal of the`
  line `application aforesaid and shall determine the charge against the accused in conformity with the result of`
  line `the application for rectification.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (1905)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1905&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the conduct of its`
  line `business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (1906)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Protection of security of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1906&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Authority`
  line `or the Registrar shall--`
  line
  line `(a) not disclose any information relating to the registration of a variety or any application relating`
  line `to the registration of a variety under this Act, which it considers prejudicial to the interest of the`
  line `security of India; and`
  line
  line `(b) take any action regarding the cancellation of registration of such varieties registered under this`
  line `Act which the Central Government may by notification in the Official Gazette specify in the interest`
  line `of the security of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "security of India" means any action`
  line `necessary for the security of India which relates to the use of any produce of any variety registered under`
  line `this Act directly or indirectly for the purposes of war or military establishment or for the purposes of war`
  line `or other emergency in international relations.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (1907)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Implied warranty on sale of registered variety, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1907&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `Where a denomination of a variety or its`
  line `propagating material or essentially derived variety or its propagating material registered under this Act`
  line `has been applied to the variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety or its propagating`
  line `material, as the case may be, on sale or in the contract for sale of such variety or its propagating material`
  line `or essentially derived variety or its propagating material, as the case may be, the seller shall be deemed to`
  line `warrant that the denomination is a genuine denomination and not falsely applied, unless the contrary is`
  line `expressed in writing signed by or on behalf of the seller and delivered at the time of the sale of the variety`
  line `or its propagating material or essentially derived variety or its propagating material, as the case may be, or`
  line `contract to and accepted by the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (1908)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Death of party to a proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1908&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `If a person who is a party to a proceeding under this Act (not`
  line `being a proceeding in a court) dies pending the proceeding, the Authority or the Registrar, as the case may`
  line `be, may, on request, and on proof to the satisfaction of such Authority or Registrar, of the transmission of`
  line `the interest of the deceased person, substitute in the proceedings his successor in interest in his place, or,`
  line `if the Authority or the Registrar is of opinion that the interest of the deceased person is sufficiently`
  line `represented by the surviving party, permit the proceedings to continue without the substitution of his`
  line `successor in interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (1909)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Right of registered agent and the registered licensee to institute suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1909&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The registered agent or`
  line `the registered licensee of a variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety or its`
  line `propagating material registered under this Act may institute appropriate proceedings in the court under`
  line `this Act on behalf of the breeder of such variety or its propagating material or essentially derived variety`
  line `or its propagating material, as the case may be, if such agent or licensee has been authorised in the`
  line `prescribed manner by such breeder for doing so.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (1910)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Evidence of entry in Register, etc., and things done by the Authority and the Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1910&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1)A copy of any entry in the Register, or of any document issued under this Act purporting to be certified`
  line `by the Authority or the Registrar and sealed with the seal of such Authority or Registrar, as the case may`
  line `be, shall be admitted in evidence in all courts and in all proceedings without further proof or production`
  line `of the original.`
  line
  line `(2) A certificate purporting to be under the hand of the Authority or the Registrar, as the case may be,`
  line `as to any entry, matter or things that such Authority or Registrar is authorised by this Act or the rules to`
  line `make or do shall be prima facie evidence of the entry having been made, and of the content thereof, or of`
  line `the matter or things having been done or not done.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (1911)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Authority, Registrar and other officers not compellable to production of Register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1911&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Authority or the Registrar or any officer working under the Authority or the Registrar, as the case may be,`
  line `shall not, in any legal proceedings, be compelled to produce the Register or any other document in its or`
  line `his custody, the content of which can be proved by the production of a certified copy issued under this`
  line `Act in the prescribed manner or to appear as a witness to prove the matter therein recorded unless by`
  line `order of the court made for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (1912)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Document open to public inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1912&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Any person may, on an application to the Authority or`
  line `the Registrar, as the case may be, and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, obtain a certified`
  line `copy of any entry in the Register or any other document in any proceedings under this Act pending before`
  line `such Authority or Registrar or may inspect such entry or document.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (1913)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Report of Authority to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1913&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause to`
  line `be placed before both Houses of Parliament once a year a report regarding the performance of the`
  line `Authority under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (1914)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Government to be bound.`
  content `The provisions of this Act shall be binding on the Government.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1914&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (1915)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Proceedings before Authority or Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1915&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `All proceedings before the Authority or the`
  line `Registrar, as the case may be, relating to registration of variety or essentially derived variety, registration`
  line `of agent, registration of licence or registration of compulsory licensing under this Act shall be deemed to`
  line `be judicial proceedings within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purpose of section 196 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Authority or the Registrar, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (1916)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1916&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, or against the Chairperson, or members, or the Registrar or any`
  line `person acting under such Government, Authority or Registrar under the provisions of this Act, for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule,`
  line `regulation, scheme or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (1917)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes `1.The words “or the Tribunal” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 23 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1917&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the`
  line `Authority or the Registrar ^1*** is empowered by or under this Act to determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (1918)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Members and staff of Authority, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1918&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, members,`
  line `officers and other employees of the Authority and the Registrar-General and the officers and other`
  line `employees working under him shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (1919)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Exemption from tax on wealth and income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1919&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (26 of 1957), the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), or any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force relating to tax on wealth, income, profits or gains, the Authority shall not be liable to`
  line `pay wealth-tax, income-tax or any other tax in respect of its wealth, income, profits or gains derived.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (1920)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1920&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (1921)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1921&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give`
  line `directions to the Authority as it may think necessary in the public interest for the execution of all or any of`
  line `the functions of the Authority under any provision of this Act or rules and regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (1922)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1922&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (1923)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1923&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) duties and jurisdiction of the Registrars under sub-section (4) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office and the conditions of service of the Registrars under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) the criteria of distinctiveness, uniformity and stability for registration of extant variety under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which a single and distinct denomination to a variety shall be assigned by the`
  line `applicant under sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) the matters governing the assignment of denomination to a variety under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(f) the time within which the Registrar may require the applicant to propose another denomination`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of application under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(h) the standards for evaluating seed during tests under sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(i) the quantity of seeds or propagating material including parental line seeds to be deposited by a`
  line `breeder and the time to be specified under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(j) the limitations and conditions subject to which a breeder may authorise a person to produce,`
  line `sell, market or otherwise deal with variety under sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(k) the form for authorisation under sub-section (3) of section 28.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (1924)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692&sectionId=1924&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00002_200153_1517807322692
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the term of office of the Chairperson and the manner of filling the post under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(ii) the salary and allowances of the Chairperson and his conditions of service in respect of leave,`
  line `pension, provident fund and other matters and the allowances for non-official members for attending`
  line `the meeting under sub-section (8) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(iii) the time and place of meetings of the Authority and the rules of procedure in regard to the`
  line `transaction of business at its meetings [including the quorum at its meetings and the transaction of`
  line `business of its Standing Committee appointed under sub-section (7) of section 3] under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(iv) the control and restriction regarding appointment of the officers and other employees of the`
  line `Authority and the method of such appointment, salary and allowances and other conditions of service`
  line `under section 6;`
  line
  line `(v) the powers and duties of the Chairperson under section 7;`
  line
  line `(vi) the terms and conditions subject to which and the manner in which the measures referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) of section 8 may provide for the registration of new extant varieties under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(vii) the manner for arranging production and sale of the seed under clause (e) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(viii) the orders by the Authority or the Registrar as to costs under clause (b) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(ix) the salary and allowances of Registrar-General of Plant Varieties and the conditions of`
  line `service in respect of his leave, pension, provident fund and other matters under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(x) the matters to be included in the National Register of Plant Varieties under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(xi) the manner of authorising a person under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(xii) the fees under clause (g) and the other particulars under clause (i) which shall accompany the`
  line `application under sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the form of application under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the period within which after making application a proof of the right to make the application`
  line `is to be furnished under sub-section (3) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(xv) the fees to be deposited by the applicant under sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the manner and method of conducting the tests under sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the manner of advertising application, conditions or limitations and specifications of variety`
  line `for registration including its photographs or drawings under sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(xviii) the manner of giving notice and the fees payable therefor under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 21;`
  line
  line `(xix) the manner of sending counter-statement under sub-section (4) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(xx) the manner of submitting evidence and the time within which such evidence may be`
  line `submitted under sub-section (6) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(xxi) the documents and fees under sub-section (1) and the tests to be conducted and the`
  line `procedure to be followed under sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(xxii) the form of a certificate of registration and the other authority to which a copy thereof shall`
  line `be sent under sub-section (8) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) the form of a certificate of registration and the other authority to which a copy thereof and`
  line `the maximum time for issuing the certificate of registration under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) the manner of giving notice to the applicant under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(xxv) the fees for review and renewal under sub-section (6) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) the contents of the certificate and the manner of publishing such contents and inviting`
  line `claim of benefits sharing under sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) the form for submitting claims of benefit sharing and the fees to be accompanied therewith`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) the manner in which and the time within which opposition to claims shall be submitted`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(xxix) the manner of making reference under sub-section (7) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(xxx) the manner of making an application for registration for title and the fees to be accompanied`
  line `therewith under sub-section (4) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxi) the manner of referring the disputes regarding registration of entitlement under the proviso`
  line `to sub-section (4) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxii) the manner to enter into a certificate the brief conditions of entitlement under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxiii) the manner of making an application for varying the terms of registration under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (9) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxiv) the manner of making an application by the registered breeder and certain other for`
  line `cancellation of terms of registration under clause (b) of sub-section (9) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxv) the manner of application by any person other than the breeder, his successor, the`
  line `registered agent or the registered licensee for cancellation of terms of registration under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (9) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxvi) the manner of application for cancellation of the terms of registration under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (9) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxvii) the manner of application for cancellation of the terms of registration under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (9) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(xxxviii) the manner of issuing notice to the registered breeder of a variety or his successor or to`
  line `each registered agent or registered licensee (not being the applicant) under sub-section (10) of section`
  line 28;
  line
  line `(xxxix) the manner of giving notice to the registrar under sub-section (1) of section 33;`
  line `(xl) the manner of notifying to the registered agent or registered licensee under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 33;`
  line
  line `(xli) the period within which the notice of opposition under sub-section (3) of section 33 may be`
  line given;
  line
  line `(xlii) the manner of making application under section 34;`
  line
  line `(xliii) the manner of depositing fees under sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(xliv) the manner of making application under sub-section (1) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(xlv) the manner of applying to the Registrar under sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(xlvi) the manner of giving notice under sub-section (4) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(xlvii) the manner of application under sub-section (1) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(xlviii) the manner of making application under sub-section (2) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(xlix) the manner to apply to the Registrar under sub-section (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of advertising application and to give notice to the Registrar, and the time from the`
  line `date of the advertisement within which a person may give such notice under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 38;`
  line
  line `(li) the manner of advertising the denomination of the variety under sub-section (3) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(lii) the manner of recognition and reward from Gene Fund under clause (iii) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 39;`
  line
  line `(liii) the manner of claiming compensation and filing of opposition under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 39;`
  line
  line `(liv) the manner of issuing notice and filing objection under sub-section (3) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(lv) the manner of receiving benefit sharing under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 45;`
  line
  line `(lvi) the manner of applying Gene Fund under sub-section (2) of section 45;`
  line
  line `(lvii) the particulars to be contained in the application under sub-section (2) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(lviii) the authority and the manner in which such authority shall make available to the`
  line `compulsory licensee the reproduction material of the variety under section 50;`
  line
  line `(lix) the form for making application under sub-section (1) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(lx) the period within which an appeal shall be preferred under sub-section (1) of section 56;`
  line
  line `(lxi) the form of petition and the particulars which such petition shall contain under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 56;`
  line
  line `(lxii ) the form for preparing annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(lxiii) the financial and administrative powers which the Chairperson shall exercise under`
  line `section 63;`
  line
  line `(lxiv) the manner of using the denomination of a variety under sub-section (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(lxv) the manner of authorising registered agent or registered licensee under section 81;`
  line
  line `(lxvi) the manner of issuing certified copy of content of Register or any other document under`
  line `section 83;`
  line
  line `(lxvii) the fees payable for obtaining a certified copy of, or to inspect, any entry in the Register or`
  line `any other document under section 84;`
  line
  line `(lxviii) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which this Act`
  line `makes no provision or makes insufficient provision and provision is, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, necessary for the proper implementation of this Act.`
